    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/giocomai/ganttrify\">R package ganttrify</a> is really suitable for Gantt chart, all we need to do is to compile the time schedual into a csv file, then read it into R, then apply the <code class=\"language-text\">ganttrify</code> function to plot it.</p>\n<p>So initially I prepared a CSV file with my Google Sheets, then pasted it into a csv file, then read it and tyde it a bit with <code class=\"language-text\">kable</code> function.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"r\"><pre class=\"language-r\"><code class=\"language-r\"><span class=\"token operator\">></span> Gantt <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;-</span> read.csv<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"./Gantt.csv\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>sep<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\\t\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">></span> knitr<span class=\"token operator\">::</span>kable<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>Gantt<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span>wp                           <span class=\"token operator\">|</span>index <span class=\"token operator\">|</span>activity                           <span class=\"token operator\">|</span>start_date <span class=\"token operator\">|</span>end_date   <span class=\"token operator\">|</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token ope